ce:section.ce:para:
The recognition property of the test strip was affected by various factors such as the amount of solvent and CDs, the molar proportion of template, functional monomer and cross-linker. The effect of the solvent amount in the reaction system was exhibited in Table 1
                        . When 10.0 mL of solvent was adopted, the test strip had a higher IF value (IF = 3.96). The molar proportion of template, functional monomer and cross-linker plays a significant role for the recognition property of the test strips, thereby a series of the test strips with the different molar proportion were prepared (Table 2
                        ). The results indicated that the fluorescent test strips based on the molar proportion of 1:8:8 exhibited the optimal recognition property. In addition, when 1.0 mL of CDs was added, the test strips possessed the optimum IF values (Table 3
                        ).
